                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 9: The countrys foreign exchange reserves fell $1.12 billion to $305.47 billion for the week ended August 1, registering a drop for the third consecutive week. Foreign currency assets (FCAs) during the week dropped $1.65 billion to $295.21 billion, the RBI said in its weekly report. The FCAs include the effect of appreciation or depreciation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen, it said.                             
	 London, Aug. 9: Pawan K. Ruia, the new owner of a Leicestershire-based engineering company, has promised the local unions that there will be no job cuts after the takeover of the UKs Metzeler Automotive Profile Systems. Ruia also announced that the company would spend 7.5 million to set up a Schlegel unit in India.                                                                                                                         
